50|$|<b>Industrial</b> <b>noise</b> is an {{occupational}} hazard linked to traditionally loud {{industries such as}} ship-building, Mining, railroad work, Welding and Construction. <b>Industrial</b> <b>noise,</b> if experienced repeatedly, at a high intensity, {{for an extended period}} of time, can cause noise-induced hearing loss (NIHL). NIHL caused by <b>industrial</b> <b>noise</b> can be classified as occupational hearing loss.|$|E
