50|$|In the United States, the National Institute for Occupational Safety and Health (NIOSH) and the Occupational Safety and Health Administration (OSHA) work {{together}} to provide standards and regulations for noise in the workplace. <b>Industrial</b> <b>noise</b> can also be regulated by legislation. A 2012 Cochrane review found low-quality evidence that legislation reduced <b>industrial</b> <b>noise</b> both immediately and in the long-term.|$|E
